natural problem: Our club has 25 members, and wishes to pick a president, secretary, and treasurer.  In how many ways can we choose the officers, if individual members may hold more than one office?
natural solution: There are 25 choices for each position, so there are $25\times 25\times 25=\boxed{15,\!625}$ ways that the positions can be filled.
